# New Feature Delivery Process

When implementing a new feature, follow this process strictly.

## Process Phases

1. Architecture overview - define layers and responsibilities.
2. File plan - list NEW and MODIFIED files with purpose, grouped by domain/ui/api.
3. Implementation - code grouped by file with clear headers.
4. Self-review - check rule compliance and list improvements.

## Mandatory Approval Gate

- Stop after phase 2 (file plan).
- Wait for explicit user confirmation before phase 3 implementation.

## Output Format (Mandatory)

1. Architecture overview
2. File plan (NEW and MODIFIED files, directory, purpose)
3. After confirmation, implementation
4. Self-review (check each architecture/styling rule)
